communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

I request access to any records related to the City of Clinton's sanitation services, including, but not limited to:

1. Any formal complaints or investigations into Clinton’s Streets & Sanitation Department from March 1, 2024 – March 1, 2025.

2. Any legal opinions, advisories, or rulings concerning the City of Clinton’s responsibility for waste collection and public sanitation.

3. Any communications or reports involving the Public Integrity Unit regarding possible negligence, misconduct, or mismanagement of sanitation services in Clinton.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Edwin Chadwick

communications.subject: South Carolina Public Records Law Request: Waste Management & Environmental Health Records for Clinton, SC
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the South Carolina Public Records Law, I hereby request the following records:

1. All sanitation-related complaints filed about Clinton from March 1, 2024 – March 1, 2025.

2. Any inspections, citations, or enforcement actions issued to the City of Clinton for waste management violations in the same period.

3. Any reports or assessments regarding public health or environmental risks caused by uncollected waste or sanitation failures in Clinton.

4. Any communications (emails, memos, meeting notes) between SC DHEC and Clinton officials regarding sanitation concerns or waste management policies.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

communications.subject: Massachusetts Public Records Law Request: All emails about Chick-fil-A shooting
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Massachusetts Public Records Law, I hereby request the following records:

Please provide all emails, reports, meeting summaries, and call summaries related to the Chick-fil-A shooting. For reference, the incident occurred on March 1. Responsive records should include any documents generated before, during, or after the incident. Given the evolving situation, I request that records be provided on a rolling basis as they become available.

I also request that, if appropriate, fees be waived as we believe this request is in the public interest, as suggested but not stipulated by the recommendations of the Massachusetts Supervisor of Public Records. The requested documents will be made available to the general public free of charge as part of the public information service at MuckRock.com, and is not made for commercial usage.

I expect the request to be filled in an accessible format, including for screen readers, which provide text-to-speech for persons unable to read print. Files that are not accessible to screen readers include, for example, .pdf image files as well as physical documents.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Brian McCarter

title: Request for Body Cam Footage of Incident

communications.subject: Florida Sunshine Law Request: Request for Body Cam Footage of Incident
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Florida Sunshine Law, I hereby request the following records:

Incident Details for Footage Retrieval:

Suspect: Christy Turman, 37
Incident Summary: Deputies responded after Turman reportedly called 911 to report that she was in the process of stealing a car from a dealership so she “could do it legally.” She allegedly stated she was training in a game of Black Ops to steal a car but contacted 911 to make the crime legal. Deputies arrested her at the scene.
I am requesting copies of all body-worn camera footage from officers who:

Responded to the initial 911 call.
Interacted with or detained Turman.
Conducted any interviews related to the incident.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Harun
